EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to preventing the use of government subsidies to rent residential properties with a record of hazardous or seriously hazardous conditions.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.4459, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.7394, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing a deferred retirement option program”.
EventItemMatterName: Deferred retirement option program (S.4459, A.7394).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.4460, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.7391, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to vested retirement rights”.
EventItemMatterName: Vested retirement rights (S.4460, A.7391).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.4442-A, and Assembly Member Pheffer, A.4683-A, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to establishing a procedure for medical review in correction member disability cases”.
EventItemMatterName: Medical review in correction member disability cases (S.4442-A, A.4683-A).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.4454, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.7111, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to reopening optional twenty-five year early retirement programs for associate park service workers and motor vehicle operators employed by the city of New York”.
EventItemMatterName: Twenty five year early retirement programs (S.4454, A.7111).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.4462, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.7610, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to health insurance coverage for surviving spouses of members of the fire department engaged in performing emergency medical services in the city of New York who are enrolled in a health insurance plan”.
EventItemMatterName: Insurance coverage for surviving spouses (S.4462, A.7610).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.5034-A, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.8214, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to disability benefits of New York City sanitation members”.
EventItemMatterName: Disability benefits of NYC sanitation members (S.5034-A, A.8214).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.3831, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.7300, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to providing a three-quarters pay accidental disability pension for persons employed by the city of New York as urban park rangers and associate urban park rangers”.
EventItemMatterName: Three quarters pay accidental pay disability pension (S.3831, A.7300).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Golden, S.5146, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing death benefits for certain beneficiaries of deceased firefighters”.
EventItemMatterName: Certain beneficiaries of deceased firefighters (S.5146).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.3829, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.6516-A, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the retirement and social security law, in relation to providing improved ordinary death benefits to emergency medical technicians employed in the city of New York”.
EventItemMatterName: Ordinary death benefits to EMTs (S.3829, A.6516-A).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member O’Donnell, A.6206, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to removing the citizenship from the required qualifications of police officers and firefighters”.
EventItemMatterName: Removing citizenship for required qualifications (A.6206).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the establishment of a Commission on Queen Mother Moore Reparations for Descendants of Africans of New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Establish a Commission on Queen Mother Moore Reparations

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the City Council to declare its support for plaintiffs Deadria Farmer-Paellmann, Mary Lacey Madison, Andrea Carrington and all others similarly situated, in their efforts to seek restitution in a federal class action suit brought against the corporations that are alleged to have participated in and directly profited from the abhorrent institution of slavery.
EventItemMatterName: Slavery, Restitution and Class Action Suit

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Board of Elections to promptly certify Precinct Based Optical Scan voting systems that are compliant with the New York State Board of Elections voting system standards for procurement by the county Boards of Elections and urging the Board of Elections in the City of New York to select a Precinct Based Optical Scan system that is compliant with the New York State Board of Elections voting system standards as the new voting technology for the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Urging the NYS Board of Elections to promptly certify precinct based/optical scan voting systems.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting the concept of the Underground Railroad Curriculum, a culturally relevant and inspiring educational tool that educates students about the contributions, accomplishments and struggles of African Americans.
EventItemMatterName: Supporting the concept of the Underground Railroad Curriculum.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the charter of the city of New York, in relation to requiring all city agencies to respond to Freedom of Information requests according to a prescribed timetable.
EventItemMatterName: Require all City agencies to respond to FOIL requests according to a prescribed timetable.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the charter of the city of New York, in relation to permitting anyone who is otherwise eligible to register and vote, and who is at least sixteen years old, to register to vote in municipal elections.
EventItemMatterName: Permitting anyone who is otherwise eligible to register and vote, and who is at least 16 years old, to register to vote in municipal elections.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York Congressional Delegation and all other members of Congress to oppose several bills that have been introduced into the 109th Congress of the United States -Senate Bills S. 1349 and S. 1504 and House of Representatives Bill  H.R. 3146-along with the proposed bill of the House of Representatives Energy and Commerce Committee entitled The Communications, Opportunity, Promotion, and Enhancement Act of 2006 (referred to as COPE”) which would amend the Communications Act of 1934 to restrict, if not eliminate, local franchising and severely undermine community programming and the implementation of universal, affordable broadband access.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Communications Act of 1934

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution denouncing President Bush’s support for the approval of Dubai Ports World to acquire six major American ports, including a key terminal in New York Harbor.
EventItemMatterName: Denouncing President Bush’s support for the approval of Dubai Ports World to acquire six major American ports, including a key terminal in NY Harbor.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to make schoolyards available for public use outside of school hours.
EventItemMatterName: Dep't of Education to hold open for public use, outside of school hours, playgrounds located on school property.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Standards and Ethics
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the annual disclosure of financial interests by certain officers and employees of or affiliated with the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Annual disclosure of financial interests by certain officers and employees of or affiliated with NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to educational requirements for appointment to the New York City Police Department.
EventItemMatterName: Educational requirements for appointment to the NYPD.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Governor to discontinue the State of New York’s delay of the collection of the sales and excise tax on the sale of cigarettes made to non-Native Americans on Native American reservations.
EventItemMatterName: Discontinue NYS delay of the collection of the sales and excise tax on the sale of cigarettes made to non-Native Americans on Native American reservations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to abating rats as a requirement for the issuance of a permit for new construction or a building alteration.
EventItemMatterName: Abating rats as a requirement for the issuance of a permit for new construction or a building alteration.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: Resolution commending the Department of Sanitation for launching “Operation N.I.C.E.” (Neighborhood Intensive Clean-Up Effort) and calling for a hearing on the results of its citywide implementation.
EventItemMatterName: “Operation N.I.C.E.” (Neighborhood Intensive Clean-Up Effort)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the appropriate committee of the Council of the City of New York to hold a hearing on implementing the recommendations of “Separate and Unequal: Medical Apartheid in New York City,” a report by Bronx Health Reach, with the goal of eliminating racial health disparities.
EventItemMatterName: Implementing the recommendations of “Separate and Unequal: Medical Apartheid in New York City.”

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to include instruction in environmental science at all appropriate grade levels of the New York City public school system.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Department of Education to include instruction in environmental science at all appropriate grade levels of the NYC public school system.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the use of ultra low sulfur diesel fuel and the best available technology for reducing the emission of pollutants by diesel fuel-powered ferries owned or operated by the city of New York.
